			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">There is no security reason to insist that the writable data segment be page-aligned.  The normal ELF layout places the writable data immediately after the rodata in the file, and at edata+PAGE_SIZE in the memory image.  This avoids bloating the file size by up to PAGE_SIZE-1.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-09-28T15:26:27.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-05-31T17:02:57.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
